notesStmt.note: Title from heading for index (f. i recto). Title on spine: Rubrica diversorum statutorum, with number B 262.

Printed document no. 136 (in Latin, 4 f.) is titled Communis Lamporecchij pecuniaria sive restitutionis in integrum; is headed with a genealogy of Luca Antonius; is signed Antonius Philippus Medices; and dated 1714.

msContents.summary: Privileges, statutes, and laws of Florence and Tuscany covering a wide range of topics: territorial divisions, customs, litigation, ecclesiastical exemption, the conduct of public officials, regulation of trade, inheritance, Jews, etc. Collection of 137 documents, both copies and originals, dated 1541-1715, most dated ca. 1650-1700, not in chronological order, each document is numbered in a contemporary hand; no. 114 (1 May 1700) and no. 136 (1714) are printed. Documents are indexed (f. i recto-viii verso).

msItem.title: Diversorum statutorum, ac legum particularum civitatis, comitatus, ac districtus florentie

support.watermark: Various, including watermark with Medici coat of arms.

supportDesc.extent: 408 leaves : 287 x 201 mm. bound to 300 x 210 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i (contemporary paper) + 408 + i (contemporary paper); [1-400]; modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto. Individual documents are numbered in a contemporary hand. Folios 48-49, 154-155, 177, and 399-400 are detached.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in various cursive scripts by many different hands.

binding.p: Contemporary parchment. Many documents are fragile, some have been trimmed with some loss of text at the edges, some oxidation of ink.

origin.p: Written in Florence; copies and original documents dated 1541-1715; manuscript itself dates from 1636-ca. 1715.
